Firefighters have been tackling large wildfires across Wales.
A helicopter helped put out a blaze on Cwmcelyn Mountain, Blaina, Blaenau Gwent, while crews tackled a fire on another mountain during the heatwave. 
Firefighters have been on Mynydd Twr mountain in Holyhead, Anglesey, after a wildfire broke out Sunday night.
Elsewhere, there have been fires at Pentre Halkyn, Flintshire and on Kilvey Hill, near Swansea. Nearby residents were advised to keep windows closed.
